We note that the dark saturation current density (j0) varies greatly across different classes of LEDs, from ~10−39 mA cm−2 for FIrpic, ~10−35 mA cm−2 for PCPB perovskite, ~10−27 mA cm−2 for F8BT, ~10−25 mA cm−2 for CdSe/ZnS to ~10−15 mA cm−2 for InGaAsP devices (Fig. 3g and Supplementary Table 2). j0 contains important information on the physics of charge recombination in LEDs, and it depends on Eg and Λ (Supplementary Note 2). The measured j0 exhibit a negative correlation with Eg. To allow a clearer comparison across different material systems, we also calculated the bandgap-weighted dark saturation current densities (j0eEgkT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
